article.headline: W. Carolina 78, Chattanooga 70
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. -- Jake Robinson scored all 18 of his points in the second half and Keaton Cole scored 15 of his 16 in the first half as Western Carolina defeated Chattanooga 78-70 on Saturday in the teams' regular-season finale. The Catamounts (21-10, 11-7 Southern Conference) have a bye into the conference tournament quarterfinals on March 6, while the Mocs (14-17, 6-12) will play a first-round game March 5. A 3-pointer by Cole capped a 15-0 run by Western Carolina to open the game, but Chattanooga closed to within 35-26 at halftime. The Mocs trailed by just three, 50-47, after a layup by Keegan Bell with 11:31 remaining, but two free throws by Kendall Russell and a 3-pointer by Robinson restored an eight-point margin, 55-47. Brigham Waginger added 15 points and four assists for the Catamounts. Ricky Taylor scored 13 points to lead the Mocs, and Bell had 12 points.
